name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. Hector LAUREANO-ALVARADO, Appellee

judges: Before FLAHERTY, C.J., and ZAPPALA, CAPPY, CASTILLE, NIGRO, NEWMAN and SAYLOR, JJ.
parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. Hector LAUREANO-ALVARADO, Appellee.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
Based upon our disposition in Commonwealth v. Williams, 557 Pa. 285, 733 A.2d 593 (1999), we affirm the Order of the Lancaster County Court of Common Pleas dated November 9, 1998. Furthermore, we remand the matter to the common pleas court for disposition of any remaining issues.
Jurisdiction is relinquished.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

attorneys: Joseph C. Madenspacher, District Attorney, Susan E. Moyer, Asst. District Attorney, District Attorney’s Office, for Com.
James J. Karl, Chief Public Defender, Public Defender’s Office, for Hector Laureano-Alvarado.
